RACE.FOOTNOTES: OHEAVENS was content to stalk near the back in the early going, shifted just off the fence at the quarter pole, began to lengthen her stride when switching leads inside the eighth pole and was full of run late to win comfortably in the end. LOADED VIXEN broke sharp to dictate the pace at the half, surrendered the front seven sixteenths from home, chased the frontrunner through the turn and was gritty between rivals in mid stretch to finish well to capture the place share. GREEN GABLES showed good speed outside to take command entering the turn, continued to separate herself from runners racing on the turn opening up as they turned for home, began to weaken at the furlong marker and faltered with seventy yards remaining. TICKLE HER TOE settled near the back on the inside in the beginning, was roused angling out three wide at the top of the lane and showed some good energy gaining late on her rivals in deep stretch. AWILDAS TREASURE sat behind the early speed pair tracking at the half, was urged on the turn to go after the leaders inside and offered little effort in the stretch drive. LINCOLNVILLE BEACH was fractious in the gate before the break, off slowly when the latch opened, trailed the pack down the backside and could not recover enough to close the gap on the field through the stretch.

MANETKA stalked outside four deep at the half, could not gain on rivals through the turn and made little impression running to the wire. TORY'S HOLIDAY was brushed outside at the break, then was steadied while leaving the chute to trail the field down the backstretch, offered a mild rally saving ground on the turn but could not be a factor racing down the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAXIMUS MOMENTUS settled inside mid pack early, started to rally midway on the turn angling outside to be in the four path when they straightened out for the drive and continued a sustained run to wear down the leaders in deep stretch. RACING IN THE RAIN broke in to begin, set all the fractions while alone on the front throughout the turn, tried to open up at the top of the lane, could not shake loose from his challengers at the furlong marker and was caught in deep stretch. FADE AWAY advanced on the rail at the half to be behind the frontrunner entering the turn, continued to chase the pace at the quarter pole, angled just outside for the drive and dug in between foes in mid stretch but could not gain late for a better placing. BLOCKBUSTER stalked close to the back three wide at the half, put in a four wide rally three furlongs from the prize outside his rivals and offered some run in the stretch passing tiring runners. DUKE OF MIAMI settled near the back of the field between horses in the early stages, was coaxed for more on the turn, could not offer a run and was not a factor running to the finish. BIG BAD BEAST chased the leader racing outside of rivals at the half, could not keep up with the front pair at the quarter pole and faded through the field in the stretch. RADCLIFFE was brushed at the start, chased the pace down the backstretch, steadied briefly and retreated quickly seven sixteenths from the finish then lost contact with the field as they turned for home. RACE.FOOTNOTES: ONE BAY HEMINGWAY was four wide fighting for the front end on the turn, put away his speed rivals as they entered upper stretch and began to edge away from all challengers the final sixteenth in an impressive score.
